ies/know-your-composer/vanraj-bhatia Vanraj Bhatia], Serenade, March 22, 2017.\n* [https://thereel.scroll.in/830547/the-vanraj-bhatia-interview-my-music-was-unique-then-and-is-perhaps-unique-even-now The Vanraj Bhatia interview: \u2018My music was unique then and is perhaps unique even now\u2019], Scroll, March 1, 2017.\n* [https://www.deccanherald.com/content/455518/bhatia.html The Best of Bhatia], Deccan Herald, January 24, 2015.\n* [https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/pV1cS0blnWIHBuXwTMa2VL/Vanraj-Bhatia--Thank-you-for-the-music.html Thank you for the music], LiveMint, April 26, 2014.\n\n{{NationalFilmAwardBestMusicDirection}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bhatia, Vanraj}}\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Elphinstone College alumni]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Academy of Music]]\n[[Category:Indian male composers]]\n[[Category:Indian film score composers]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Sangeet Natak Akademi Award]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Shri in arts]]\n[[Category:Hindi film score composers]]\n[[Category:Best Music Direction National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Conservatoire de Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Rockefeller Fellows]]\n[[Category:Jingle composers]]\n[[Category:Pupils of Nadia Boulanger]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian musicians]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n", "name_user": "ShwetantKumar", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanraj_Bhatia"}
{"title_page": "Carrickfergus Borough Council", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2012}}\n{{coord|54.721|-5.791|region:GB_scale:20000|display=title}}\n{{Infobox UK place\n\n| official_name            = Carrickfergus Borough (historical)\n| local_name               = Comhairle Baile Charraig Fheargais\n| country                  = Northern Ireland\n| static_image_name        = \n| static_image_2_name      = Carrickfergus in Northern Ireland.svg\n| area_total_km2           = 82\n| area_footnotes           = \n| statistic_title          = \n| statistic                = \n| statistic_title1         = \n| statistic1               = \n| statistic_title2         = \n| statistic2               = \n| councillor1              = \n| councillor2              = '''[[List of MPs elected in the 2010 United Kingdom general election|MPs]]'''<br>[[Sammy Wilson (politician)|Sammy Wilson]] (DUP)\n| website                  = \n| hide_services            = yes\n}}\n'''Carrickfergus Borough Council''' was a district council in [[County Antrim]] in [[Northern Ireland]]. It merged with [[Ballymena Borough Council]] and [[Larne Borough Council]] in May 2015 under local government reorganisation in Northern Ireland to become [[Mid and East Antrim Borough Council]].\n\nThe council headquarters were in [[Carrickfergus]] and the council administered the town, on the north shore of [[Belfast Lough]], and surrounding area, which extended from [[Greenisland]] in the south-west to [[Whitehead, Northern Ireland|Whitehead]] in the east. The borough was {{convert|32|sqmi|km2}}, with a population of just over 39,000.\n\nTogether with the neighbouring district of [[Larne Borough Council|Larne]] and small parts of [[Newtownabbey Borough Council|Newtownabbey]] and [[Moyle District Council|Moyle]], it formed the [[East Antrim (disambiguation)|East Antrim constituency]] for elections to the [[Westminster Parliament]] and [[Northern Ireland Assembly]].\n\n==